race.comment: DIVINE THOUGHTS (8) resumes for the McEvoys and has switched from the Moody-Coleman stable. She's had a string of jumpouts and has raced well in stronger metro contests. Goes on the fresh side, and no surprise to see her wound up. The betting will be key. GEFFINA (7) improved again, beaten 2L over 1400m at Bendigo. Peaks and has the ability to fight out the finish.  FLYING FIZZ (4) brought solid city form and was expected to win this grade at Horsham. She got a long way back and disappointed (vet cleared). Yendall sticks aboard and she will be fitter again. Notably, the blinkers are applied for the first time. BILLIE BRONX (6) scored last start at Warrnambool to make it two wins from three starts this campaign. Has good early toe and is well in the mix.
